statement.tex:
\text{For what value of k would }\\
f(x) = \begin{cases}
  k\cdot x^2, x\leq 2, \\
  3, x\gt 2
\end{cases}
\\ \text{be continuous at }x=2?

step.tex:
\begin{align}
  \lim_{x\to 2^-}f(x) &= \lim_{x\to 2^-}k\cdot x^2 = 4k \\
  \lim_{x\to 2^+}f(x) & \lim_{x\to 2^+}3 = 3 \\
  f(2) &= k\cdot 2^2 = 4k 
\end{align}
\\ \text{And hence, for continuity at }x=2 \\
\begin{align}
4k &= 3 \implies k = \dfrac{3}{4}
\end{align}
